Commentary: full and wide at 142km/h and Marsh flays it uppishly through point. Shan Masood dives in the deep to save runs

Commentary: pushed down towards his legs, and they find a single off the pad

Commentary: beaten on the back foot outside off stump. Finch just swished inside it, and he's upset with himself

Commentary: Hasnain targets the stumps at almost 139km/h, Finch finding a single with a bottom-handed push into the leg side
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Finch, 1 run

Commentary: direct hit would have had him! Marsh taps to point and sets off. Finch sends him back, but he's slow to turn, and had the throw been accurate, he would have been out. Tough chance, just the one stump to aim at for Imam
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Marsh, no run

Commentary: seaming in off a length, and Finch can't get it past midwicket

Commentary: chipped uppishly into the leg side, and again midwicket cuts it off but they take him on for a quick single. The throw goes wide. And was possibly to the wrong end, as Marsh had hesitated setting off from the other end. A better throw could have made things interesting
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Finch, 1 run

Commentary: Marsh pulls, but it doesn't come onto the bat and he can't beat the infield
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Marsh, no run

Commentary: in the air, but safe! Marsh looks to pull in the air, but it rushes on to him and loops off the splice ... but falls safely at mid on! If long on had been up, that would have been the simplest of catches
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Marsh, 1 run

Commentary: just short of Yasir in the deep! Finch goes on the attack now, lifting a length ball over the leg side. He doesn't connect well, but that actually saves him as Yasir can't get in off the midwicket boundary in time to catch it - though he stops the boundary
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Finch, 2 runs

Commentary: pushed down to long on, just the one
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Finch, 1 run

Commentary: well bowled! Hasnain slings down a quick yorker at the toes, Finch hurrying to keep it out. That just tailed in through the air as well ...
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Finch, 1 run

Commentary: short, and it's pulled just wide of mid on. Haris Sohail is in position there, and he has a shy but misses. There have been a few nervy runs in the last few minutes
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Marsh, 1 run

Commentary: this will help! Finch picks up the length early, getting under the ball to swat it in the air and over the leg side boundary
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Finch, SIX runs

Commentary: another reverse swinging yorker at 144.6km/h, but it's dug out down the ground for a single

Commentary: Marsh is forward and slaps a fluid drive out to the sweeper after Hasnain aims full
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Marsh, 1 run

Commentary: pitched right up at a shade over 145km/h, and Finch drives straight to cover. They take on Haris Sohail in the position for a single, and Finch wasn't even in the frame as the throw came in ... but again it goes wide!

Commentary: spanked straight back down the ground, and Finch equals his highest score in ODI cricket

Commentary: 150 up for Aaron Finch! He gets there from 141 deliveries, flicking the ball sweetly through square leg. Back to back tons, and a career best

Commentary: pushed through mid on, just the one

Commentary: tip-and-run single, Marsh dead-batting it close on the off side and Finch calling him through
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Marsh, 1 run

Commentary: Finch misses his flick, but the ball pings off his pad and rolls to fine leg. They're back for the second, and that's the game!
